<br>
This is a pretty sad day for paper-based roleplaying, sincetheir system was one of the most highly detailed out there. I wrote an email to the chap that runs/ran ICE, and today gotback the response below.<br>
<br>
If you care even an iota aboutRoleMaster etc., please give it the once over and spend justa couple of minutes tapping an email out, and hopefully the roleplayingcommunity will continue to have the chance to buy their greatproducts.<br>
<br>
Cheers all<br>
<br>
Githnaur Ainaroquen<br>
<br>
************************************************************<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Hi,<br>
<br>
Thank you for your letterof sympathy and support. ICE could not have <br>
survived overthe years without the support of our fans. Hearing from fans,<br>
via email, over the phone, and at cons was the greatestpart of the ICE <br>
experience. It was always amazing to methat we were able to create games <br>
that other people enjoyed.Now that ICE is gone, each email I receive from <br>
one of ourcustomers is a sorrowful reminder that the best part of my ICE<br>
experience is ending.<br>
<br>
If you wish to help ICE andto continue buying ICE products, there is <br>
something thatyou can do:<br>
<br>
The chapter 7 trustee has the authorityto permit the sale of ICE products.<br>
<br>
So it's simple.<br>
Write to  icepbx@aol.com and tell us that you are interestedin buying our <br>
products. <br>
Be specific: Rolemaster, SilentDeath, Spacemaster, and Middle-earth. Mention <br>
specific products.We will forward these letters to the trustee.  What's <br>
more,ask your friends who are ICE fans to write to us as well.  Themore <br>
support we get, the greater the chance there is ofsalvaging our games from <br>
the ruins.<br>
<br>
<br>
It needsto be made absolutely and overwhelming clear to the Chapter 7<br>
trustee that all of ICE's intellectual properties and inventoryare worth a <br>
lot money. The more valuable the property, thebetter for ICE and the better <br>
for you, our fans.<br>
<br>
<br>
If the trustee knows that people what to buy these products,then there is an <br>
excellent chance that he will allow thesales of the products while the <br>
chapter 7 process continues.<br>
<br>
Don't let our games die!<br>
<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Heike Kubasch<br>
ICE founder<br>
Ex webmaster<br>
